article_title: Cyclical Stocks Are Making a Comeback
article_text:
Materials, technology, industrial and consumer-goods companies are reporting stronger-than-expected profit growth, underscoring their appeal to investors amid an expanding global economy.

Firms that sell goods and services beyond the basic necessities, which customers tend to buy when times are more flush, are on pace for the best earnings growth in the S&P 500. Third-quarter profit in this so-called consumer-discretionary sector...
